tags.name: expansion-panel
tags.description: A custom element similar to the HTML5 `<details>` element.
tags.jsDoc:
/**
 * A custom element similar to the HTML5 `<details>` element.
 *
 * @element expansion-panel
 *
 * @slot - Slot fot panel content
 * @slot header - Slot for panel header
 *
 * @attr {Boolean} focused - State attribute set when element has focus.
 * @attr {Boolean} focus-ring - State attribute set when focused from keyboard.
 *
 * @cssprop --panel-header-background - Default panel header background color.
 * @cssprop --panel-header-min-height - Panel header minimum height.
 * @cssprop --panel-ripple-background - Active toggle button ripple background.
 *
 * @csspart header - An element wrapping the `header` slot.
 * @csspart toggle - A toggle button, child of the header part.
 * @csspart content - An element wrapping the `content` slot.
 *
 * @fires opened-changed - Event fired when expanding / collapsing
 */

attributes.name: focused
attributes.description: State attribute set when element has focus.

attributes.name: focus-ring
attributes.description: State attribute set when focused from keyboard.

attributes.name: opened
attributes.description: When true, the panel content is expanded and visible

attributes.name: disabled
attributes.description: Disabled panel can not be expanded or collapsed

properties.name: opened
properties.description: When true, the panel content is expanded and visible

properties.name: disabled
properties.description: Disabled panel can not be expanded or collapsed

cssParts.name: toggle
cssParts.description: A toggle button, child of the header part.

tags.name: fancy-accordion
tags.description: A custom element wrapping several `<expansion-panel>` elements.
tags.jsDoc:
/**
 * A custom element wrapping several `<expansion-panel>` elements.
 *
 * @element fancy-accordion
 *
 * @slot - Slot fot panel elements.
 *
 * @fires opened-changed - Event fired when expanding / collapsing
 */

attributes.name: opened
attributes.description: The index of the currently opened panel.

properties.name: opened
properties.description: The index of the currently opened panel.

tags.name: progress-bar
tags.description: A custom element similar to the HTML5 `<progress>` element.
tags.jsDoc:
/**
 * A custom element similar to the HTML5 `<progress>` element.
 *
 * @element progress-bar
 *
 * @cssprop --progress-bar-fill-color - Color of the filled progress bar part.
 * @cssprop --progress-bar-opacity - Opacity set on the underlying track.
 *
 * @csspart bar - A progress bar background.
 * @csspart value - A progress bar foreground.
 */

attributes.name: min
attributes.description: Minimum bound of the progress bar.

attributes.name: max
attributes.description: Maximum bound of the progress bar.

attributes.name: indeterminate
attributes.description:
Indeterminate state of the progress bar.
This property takes precedence over other state properties (min, max, value).
attributes.jsDoc:
